Bukayo Saka is set to sign a new long-term contract at Arsenal, according to the UK Mirror. The England U19 international, who is eligible to play for Nigeria, is close to agreeing fresh terms with the Premier League club. Saka has become a consistent starter under Unai Emery this season and was picked for the Gunners’ last three league games against Aston Villa, Manchester United and Bournemouth. The Hale End Academy product signed scholarship forms with Arsenal in July 2018 along with goalkeeper Arthur Okonkwo and Ryan Alebiousu. Saka then penned his first professional contract two months later, after celebrating his 17th birthday. He joined Arsenal’s Hale End Academy at the age of eight. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.